Telkom’s group executive for communication, Jacqui O’Sullivan, has reportedly resigned from Telkom and will move to MTN. MyBroadband has received information that O’Sullivan has already tendered her resignation. Telkom said it will issue a statement soon on the matter. O’Sullivan could not be reached for comment. TechCentral reported that O’Sullivan will join MTN on “1 October after three months of gardening leave”. O’Sullivan joined Telkom on 15 September 2014 as managing executive for communication and PR. Before joining Telkom, she served as VP for group corporate branding and communication at Sasol. She was also previously the head of communication at SAA.